T: R^3 \to R^2
\qquad c_1T\alpha_1+c_2T\alpha_2 = T(c_1\alpha_1+c_2\alpha_2)
T(1,-1,1)=(1,0)\qquad T(1,1,1)=(0,1)
\Bbb R^3
T:\Bbb R^3\to\Bbb R^2
 v_1= \begin{bmatrix} 1\\-1\\1 \end{bmatrix},\quad v_2= \begin{bmatrix} 1\\1\\1 \end{bmatrix},\quad v_3= \begin{bmatrix} 1\\0\\0 \end{bmatrix} 
 T(v_1)= e_1,\quad T(v_2)=e_2,\quad T(v_3)=\mathbf 0 
T
 T \begin{bmatrix} x\\y\\z \end{bmatrix}= \frac{1}{2} \begin{bmatrix} -y +z \\ y+z \end{bmatrix} 
